reviews.review_text:
A Grateful Dead Symphony Of the "beautiful" music.

Revealed here now in Healy's front of hall mix so utterly taper precise.

On the SBD (Dicks Picks 9) the keyboards, running direct thru the PA, are annoyingly at times overblown, but in this recording they are prominent where they need be and subtle when called. All the rest of the instruments (guitars and drums) are pleasingly up-mix and well separated.

Bass guitar is eminently delicious and profound throughout. Phil's attack is so strong that it leads the band in whatever direction chosen for the moment.

And Bruce's piano chords maketh a hard man weep deep to the bone right thru his baseball cap. And causeth rain to come up from the earth.
